Accident * -> 1 AccidentType
An AccidentType has some Accidents. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.
An Accident has An AccidentType. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one AccidentType.
When an Accident is created, its AccidentType must be assigned. When an Accident is deleted, its AccidentType is not deleted and its list of Accidents is decreased. When an AccidentType is deleted, its Accidents are not deleted. They are assigned to another AccidentType.
